        "created_at": "2018-03-23T23:51:15.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Gained most votes for wine of the day in strong Company yesterday.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/wine.asp?iWine=208777\"><strong>2004 Domaine Leroy Nuits St. Georges</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Nuits, Nuits St. Georges (3/23/2018)</em><br>\nQuite cloudy and browning off like so many '04\u2019s. Thoroughly engaging nose of rose petals, lillies, sandalwood, mirepoix and Hoisin. It is lacy in the mouth, with crunchy red fruits and simmering beef stock flavours. There\u2019s some freshly grated ginger too. If one has to be critical, the palate is a tad lean and acidity a little tart on the finish, but a lovely drink none the less.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 5,
