      {
        "id": 2384101,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-03-25T01:30:27.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Gerhard P.\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n Gerhard P.:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I had this wine at about age 4y \u2026 it contains also the declassified 1er crus.<br>\nI wasn\u00b4t impressed then, actually quite disapointed \u2026 too green, too short, too devoid of ripe fruit, quite browning \u2026<br>\nIf it is now (only) a \u201clovely drink\u201d \u2026 I think that\u00b4s still not enough for the half fortune a bottle is/was on the market \u2026</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I think the hype generated by the various communal bottlings also containing the declassified higher appellations got a little carried away. In the end, the wines are very tasty, but one can see why Lalou chose to declassify. I was last served one of them blind a couple of years ago, and mortified the generous friend who\u2019d brought it be calling it as a very nice Oregon Pinot Noir.</p>",
